{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff99e4eb-ec96-4bcd-a993-d1e1365f4606","content":"For NativeAOT, the key is `DOTNET_CreateDumpPath` — since NativeAOT doesn't bundle `createdump`, you must tell the runtime where to find it. You also need the `SYS_PTRACE` capability for `createdump` to read process memory.\n\nHere are the pod spec changes:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... existing config ...\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"                          # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n        - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"      # Required for NativeAOT\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]                 # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi                        # adjust to your memory footprint\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_CreateDumpPath`** is critical for NativeAOT — without it the runtime can't locate `createdump` and silently skips dump generation.\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required because `createdump` uses `ptrace()` to snapshot the process.\n- **`emptyDir`** works for ephemeral collection; swap for a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- **`sizeLimit`** — set this to at least your container's memory limit since a full dump (`type=4`) can approach that size.\n- Use **type `2` (Heap)** instead of `4` if you want smaller dumps that still include managed heap data.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"522d73b8-57a8-4403-8b76-c6be5bfc9606","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Empty directory. The user just wants guidance on configuring crash dump collection for their NativeAOT .NET 11 app. Let me provide the pod spec changes they need.\n\nKey things for NativeAOT crash dumps:\n\n1. **`DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`** — enables crash dump on unhandled exception/crash\n2. **`DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4`** — Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n3. **`DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t`** — dump path with PID and timestamp placeholders\n\n\n4. **`DOTNET_CreateDumpPath=/opt/tools/createdump`** — points to the createdump tool since NativeAOT doesn't bundle it with the runtime\n5. **`SYS_PTRACE` capability** — required because createdump uses ptrace to access process memory\n6. A volume mount for persistent dump storage\n\nNow I'll put together a concrete pod spec example showing these environment variables, the capability, and the volume configuration.","outputTokens":820,"requestId":"981E:1E6E:8E25E1:A872C5:69F4065C"},"id":"45f9c630-0d75-4a14-aa21-8b24ce89431b","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:48:27.169Z","parentId":"87db3609-e3ab-4c98-8c7e-9576191f3f49"}
